## Architecture: Clean 3-Layer

```
HTTP Handler в†’ Domain Service в†’ Repository в†’ Database (SQLite/GORM)
```

- **Handlers**: Parse HTTP, call service, return JSON. No business logic.
- **Services**: Validation, business rules. Independent of HTTP.
- **Repositories**: GORM CRUD. Convert between API models в†” DB entities.

## Key Patterns

### Model vs Entity
- **API Models** (`models/generated.go`): `Id` (lowercase d), `*PetStatus` enum, pointer fields
- **DB Entities** (`database/entities.go`): `ID` (uppercase), string status, manual fields (not `gorm.Model` embed)
- Conversion happens in repository layer: `toModel()` / entity creation

### Error Responses
All errors return JSON: `{"error": "message"}`
- 400: Bad request / invalid input
- 404: Not found (`gorm.ErrRecordNotFound`)
- 422: Validation failed
- 500: Internal error

### Code Generation
```bash
# All commands run from backend/ directory
cd backend

# Regenerate models from spec
oapi-codegen -config oapi-codegen.yaml petstore_swagger.yml

# Regenerate Swagger docs from code annotations
swag init -g cmd/api/main.go --output docs --parseDependency --parseInternal
```

## API Endpoints

### Pet (6 endpoints)
| Method | Path | Handler |
|--------|------|---------|
| POST | `/pet` | AddPet |
| PUT | `/pet` | UpdatePet |
| GET | `/pet/findByStatus?status=` | FindPetsByStatus |
| GET | `/pet/:petId` | GetPetByID |
| POST | `/pet/:petId` | UpdatePetWithForm |
| DELETE | `/pet/:petId` | DeletePet |

### Category (4 endpoints)
| Method | Path | Handler |
|--------|------|---------|
| POST | `/category` | AddCategory |
| PUT | `/category` | UpdateCategory |
| GET | `/category/listAll` | GetAllCategories |
| DELETE | `/category/:categoryId` | DeleteCategory |

### Other
- `GET /health` - Health check
- `GET /swagger/*` - Swagger UI

**Note**: DELETE /category exists in code but NOT in `petstore_swagger.yml`. It was added outside the design-first workflow.

## Frontend (CSR)

- **Alpine.js only**: Frontend uses Alpine.js + `fetch()` for all API calls (HTMX is NOT used)
- **Static serving**: `app.Static("/", "../ui")` - files served as-is, no SSR
- **Error handling**: Backend returns `{"error": "msg"}`, UI checks `error.error`
- **Design**: Tailwind CSS via CDN with gradients, glassmorphism, animations

## Testing

```bash
cd backend
go test ./tests/integration/... -v  # All integration tests
```
- Each test gets fresh in-memory SQLite via `setupTestApp(t)`
- Tests cover: happy path, validation errors, 404s

## Dependencies (go.mod)

```
github.com/gofiber/fiber/v2 v2.52.11
github.com/gofiber/swagger v1.1.1
gorm.io/gorm v1.25.7
github.com/glebarez/sqlite v1.11.0  # Pure Go, no CGO
```

## Guidelines

- Always refer to `petstore_swagger.yml` for field names and types
- Generated models use `Id` not `ID` - this is oapi-codegen convention
- Use `string(*pet.Status)` when saving PetStatus enum to DB
- Handle errors explicitly, never ignore them
- Add Swagger annotations to all new handlers
- Write integration tests for new endpoints
